The paper discusses the development of a tool for translating the Linux kernel's kconfig model into a propositional formula, which involves variational analyses and differential testing. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Software Engineering (cs.SE) sub-category, as well as Programming Languages (cs.PL) and Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO) sub-categories, which are closely related to software development and analysis. The paper also touches on system design and verification, which could place it in the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the use of differential testing, which is a technique for detecting bugs in software, and could therefore be relevant to the Formal Languages and Automata Theory (cs.FL) sub-category.
